The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of integer programming, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of tree-depth and branch-depth suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mention of matroids and row operations suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) which deal with combinatorial optimization and linear algebra respectively. Finally, the mention of fixed parameter tractability suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
